entry.title: hibernate: Fix enabled check bug
entry.content:
When testing if a feature is enabled using base::FeatureList it's

expected that the features have already been loaded. For user only

features such as those overridden by chrome://flags then will live in the

users cryptohome. This is problematic with hibernate because we need

them during the signin process so we can start the resume process.



This change makes a few changes to how hibernate works. To start we just

store the user auth id until the user's profile has been created by the

browser process. Once the profile has been created and preferences

loaded we will notify the HibernateManager to notify the hiberman

daemon.



BUG=b:293895107

entry.title: Revert "base::RandBytes: switch implementation to BoringSSL"
entry.content:
This reverts commit 7e52c8d2ca17f7f5c7b6e6b25e4211624cb54b2b.



Reason for revert: Suspected of causing Win10 Tests x64 (dbg)

setup_unittests WriteToDiskTest.LargeData to become flaky.



The first failure was https://ci.chromium.org/ui/p/chromium/builders/ci/Win10%20Tests%20x64%20(dbg)/36680/overview.

This change is in the blamelist at

https://ci.chromium.org/ui/p/chromium/builders/ci/Win10%20Tests%20x64%20(dbg)/36680/blamelist.



The test uses base::RandBytes

(https://chromium.googlesource.com/chromium/src/+/8c47048dfb90e396bd17fbd889a5f8d383de3e88/chrome/installer/mini_installer/write_to_disk_unittest.cc#57).



Original change's description:

> base::RandBytes: switch implementation to BoringSSL

>

> On POSIX:

>

> 1. Remove the experiments to compare the RAND_bytes (from BoringSSL)

> with getrandom(2).

>

> 2. Simplify to remove getrandom(2) entirely. This leads to

> base::internal::RandDoubleAvoidAllocation() not being able to use

> faster fallbacks: getrandom(2) on Linux/Android and getentropy(3) on

> MacOS. These calls should not happen often in the field, so the

> platform-specific conditional compilation with runtime kernel version

> detection needed for those fallbacks are not worth keeping.

>

> On Windows and Fuchsia: Remove the BoringSSL experiment in the most

> straightforward way.

>

> Also remove the experiment from the fieldtrial_testing_config.

>

entry.title: DOM Parts speed optimization patch 4/N
entry.content:
This CL revamps two small parts of DOM Parts:

1. If Mutation Events are enabled, assume PartRoot parts lists are

dirty during DOM mutations. Without this, it would be possible for

a mutation event to modify the DOM and violate many of the

assumptions made during Part moves.

2. The RebuildPartsList() function previously iterated the entire

tree under nested ChildNodeParts, simply ignoring all contained

Nodes. Revamp this loop so that it skips directly from the start

to the end, and avoids iterating any of the contained tree.



These changes are covered by the existing

basic-dom-part-objects.tentative.html test.

entry.title: fix deleting autocomplete issues mouse move.
entry.content:
Problem: Deleting an autocomplete row can lead to the popup being rendered underneath the cursor, due to no OnMouseEnter event, the cell is always unhighlighted/unselected unless the users makes a movement or uses the cursor.



Solution: Listen to placeholder being painted in the screen and checking if the row or button are being hovered them.



1. We need to override views GetPreferredHeightForWith because

box_layout overrides it and returns 0 height for views that have no

visible children when the orientation is not vertical (in this case

horizontal).

2. It is possible then to override the OnPaint method of the placeholder

to check if its row is being hovered, if so, we make the butto

visible.

3. We listen to button bounds change to finally emit a mouse event. This

mouse event will select the cell (as if the user had moved it) and we

after that still need to check if the cursor is hovering the now

visible button. If so, we unselect the cell and highlight the button.

entry.title: [iOS] Fix Upgrade Promo experimental flag
entry.content:
Upgrade Promo experimental flag was introduced in crrev.com/c/4755926.

The issue with this first patch, the experimental flag was forcing

the upgrade promo before testing other parameters in -[SceneController

shouldPresentSigninUpgradePromo].

The upgrade promo was triggered by testers while there is no identity.

The promo is not supposed to be opened in that case, it was triggering

a DCHECK in `-[SceneController tryPresentSigninModalUI]`.



This patch moves the experimental flag from SceneController to

ShouldPresentUserSigninUpgrade(). With this fix, the Upgrade promo

won't be forced when it is not possible to display it.

entry.title: Only call AutofillPopupDelegate::OnPopupShown if popup was shown.
entry.content:
Prior to this change, AutofillPopupControllerImpl::Show does not return

early if AutofillPopupView::Show does not result in actually showing

the popup.



This means that AutofillPopupControllerImpl::Show will call

AutofillPopupDelegate::OnPopupShown even though

- The popup was never shown.

- AutofillPopupDelegate::OnPopupHidden was called just before it,

since failure to show the popup results in PopupViewViews

calling Hide() on the controller and the controller calls

OnPopupHidden.



Bug: 1469871

entry.title: Add usecounters for ORB-blocks and event handlers.
entry.content:
This adds three use counters for ORB-blocked resources whose loading

triggers onload or onerror event handlers. The goal is to assess the

compatibility risk of changing ORB blocking behaviour from injecting

an empty response (ORB "v0.1" and current) to raising a network error

(ORB "v0.2" and what the standards proposal wants) for non-script-initiated fetches.



This change & the use counters are temporary and are meant to be

removed once ORB "v0.2" has launched.



Bug: 1463725
